High intake of sugar is bad for health,sugary drinks like carbonated drinks,fruit juice etc,are high in sugar which means they are high in calories,avoid sugary drinks if you want to lose weight.

Make sure you follow a healthy diet,a healthy diet for weight loss includes fruits, vegetables, healthy fats, protein rich foods and fibrous foods,a healthy diet contains foods which are low in calories and helps in weight loss.

Black coffee contains caffeine which increases your metabolism and makes you energetic,consumption of black coffee helps to burn calories,do not add sugar or any high-calorie sweeteners to your coffee,drinking black coffee regularly results in weight loss.
Eggs are high in protein and low in calories,eating whole eggs for breakfast makes you full and reduces cravings for more food which helps in weight loss.

Drinking water helps in weight loss,drinking sufficient quantity of water boosts metabolism and helps to burn calories in your body,the quantity of water intake per day for adult male is 4 liters and for adult female is 3 liters.

Green tea contains caffeine and a flavonoid called catechin,catechin helps to break down excess fat in your body,the Caffeine present in green tea boosts your metabolism and helps to burn calories which results in weight loss.
Eat around 4 to 5 dates as a snack,dates are rich in fiber and low in calories,dates makes you feel full and this reduces cravings for more food which results in weight loss.
Eat fiber rich fruits like Oranges, Strawberries, Banana etc,during brunch,fruits rich in fiber makes you feel full which reduces cravings for more food and this results in weight loss.

Make sure you eat carbohydrates in their original form,consume less refined carbohydrates like red rice, whole wheat bread, whole wheat pasta and oats,less refined carbohydrates are rich in fiber and makes you feel full which reduces cravings for more food and this helps in weight loss.
Consume carbohydrates in their original form

Vegetable salads are low in calories and rich in fiber which helps you to lose weight,prepare vegetable salads using beans, olive oil, lemon juice, vinegar, pepper and leafy greens like lettuce, spinach, kale etc.
Include vegetable salads in your diet
High stress levels causes weight gain,feeling stressed results in cravings for junk foods like sweet, pizza, burgers, doughnuts etc,perform activities like yoga to keep your stress under control.

Performing cardio exercises like running, cycling, swimming, jumping rope etc,helps you to burn calories,cardio exercises also reduces belly fat in your body,Belly fat decreases your metabolism and causes weight gain,do cardio exercises regularly to lose weight.

Cook food using healthy oils like olive oil, avocado oil and sesame oil,these oils are low in calories unlike other refined oils and helps to lose weight,make sure that you use only a small quantity of these oils while cooking.
Processed foods are high in calories and causes weight gain,avoid processed foods like cheese, canned fruit, canned meat, jams, ketchup etc., if you want to lose weight.
Any food fried using refined oils are high in calories,make sure you consume steam cooked or grilled foods which are low in calories if you want to lose weight.

Eat snacks which are rich in fiber and proteins,also make sure that the snacks are low in calories,some of the healthy snacks include Greek yogurt, nuts, peanut butter, whole wheat bread, apple slices etc.
Dark chocolate can be used as a snack,dark chocolate contains healthy fats which makes you full for a long time and reduces cravings resulting in weight loss.

Chewing food slowly during a meal reduces the calorie intake and also increases the hormones related to weight loss,also make sure that you chew your food thoroughly while eating if you want to lose weight.
Adding spices to food helps to burn calories and boost your metabolism,some of the spices which helps in weight loss includes Turmeric, Cinnamon, Cumin seeds, Ginger, Garlic and black pepper.
Flax seeds are rich in proteins and fiber,flax seeds boosts metabolism and makes you feel full for a long time which helps to reduce cravings for food and helps in weight loss.

Doing yoga regularly helps us to lose weight,performing yoga helps to burn calories and also improves your metabolism,some of the yoga postures for weight loss are bow pose, child’s pose, triangle pose, twisted chair pose, Surya namaskara etc.

It is required to know about your calorie intake every day,use a calorie counter to calculate your calorie intake,your calorie intake depends on several factors like gender, age, weight, height, activities etc,on an average a woman needs 2000 calories per day to maintain the existing weight and about 1500 calories per day to lose one pound in a week,on an average a man needs 2500 calories per day to maintain the existing weight and about 2000 calories per day to lose one pound in a week.
Keep track on the calorie count
Junk foods are high in sugar,calories and unhealthy fats which causes weight gain,avoid junk foods like pizza, hot dog, French fries, hamburger etc. for weight loss.

Exercising with your friends is not just fun but also motivates you to lose weight,a study on obesity found that people who are overweight tend to lose weight if they are in the company of fit friends.
Walking helps to burn calories,make sure you walk regularly at a brisk pace if you want to lose weight,walking also helps you to lose belly fat which results in weight loss.
There are foods which are high in added sugar,these foods are high in calories and results in weight gain,avoid foods like candy, pastries, doughnuts, desserts etc,if you want to lose weight.
Foods which are high in protein boosts your metabolism and helps to burn calories in your body,protein rich foods makes you full and reduces cravings for food which helps in weight loss.
It is required to sleep for at least 7 to 8 hours a day,sleep deprivation leads to cravings for junk food which causes weight gain,make sure you get adequate sleep if you want to lose weight.
Consume foods rich in fiber like fruits, vegetables, beans, legumes, grains and nuts,fibrous foods are low in calories and also makes you full which helps in weight loss.
Reduce the intake of foods containing carbohydrates in your diet,consumption of more carbohydrates results in weight gain as they are stored as fat in your body.
